Just caught this on the forums and it seemed worthy of a post... post...<br/><br/><em class="newsquote">After a lot of bargaining, a few illicit backroom deals, three dozen bottles of budweiser, the occasional mafia hit and a LARGE amount of happymeals, the Online Warfare Pact has moved to a new domain - <a href="http://www.onlinewarfarepact.org/" target="_blank">http://www.onlinewarfarepact.org</a>.<br/><br/><br/>The domain should be easier for people to identify in search engines, and for members to be able to pass on.<br/><br/>This marks an exciting time for our organisation, as we expand and move into new areas. We will be carrying with us our comrades in arms, the Forum Fighters and you can expect to see further subdomains opening up soon to reflect the diverse player base and the games that our members play.<br/><br/>The [OwP] is an organisation encouraging clan members and individuals to meet, have games and compete in a friendly and fun atmosphere. Our aims are achieved by implementation of player and admin codes of conduct, and we have affiliated servers and gaming service providers across the world, providing player-friendly and happy environments for our members to enjoy!<br/><br/>Individuals, clans, GSPs and servers can be registered as [OwP] affiliates, by going to the signup pages on the main site.<br/><br/>Registered admins and servers will have exclusive access to our top quality coding development team's research and output, for instance, work is currently at early stages on a player name/tag registration and verification system, which when completely will be made available to interested affiliates.<br/><br/>Whether you are a high flying competitive clan with a penchant for teamplay tactics, or an absolute brand new member of the community looking for some gameplay tips and maybe some buddies, you will find bucketloads of useful info and plenty of friendly faces at The Online Warfare Pact.</em><br/></p>
